%5B%7B%22title%22%3A%22Bad%20news%2C%20star%20employees%3A%20You're%20not%20the%20ones%20who'll%20benefit%20the%20most%20from%20AI%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224151%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Colleagues%20having%20meeting%20in%20boardroom%2C%20businessman%20giving%20speech%2C%20blurred%20photo%20-%20stock%20photo%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65080267f05aa00019bdf1a5%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223113%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EBad%20news%2C%20star%20employees%3A%20You're%20not%20the%20ones%20who'll%20benefit%20the%20most%20from%20AI%3Cp%3EGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EConsultants%20using%20AI%20completed%20tasks%20faster%20and%20produced%20higher-quality%20results%20than%20those%20without%2C%20according%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fpapers.ssrn.com%2Fsol3%2Fpapers.cfm%3Fabstract_id%3D4573321%5C%22%3Ea%20new%20study.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThe%20greatest%20gains%20were%20seen%20by%20below-average%20performers%20using%20AI%2C%20per%20the%20study's%20authors.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EA%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fai-tool-barely-helped-productivity-high-skilled-experienced-workers-study-2023-5%5C%22%3Eprevious%20study%3C%2Fa%3E%20showed%20that%20AI%20assistance%20had%20a%20weak%20impact%20on%20higher-skilled%20customer%20service%20workers.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EA%20recent%20study%20conducted%20at%20management%20consulting%20firm%20Boston%20Consulting%20Group%2C%20or%20BCG%2C%20found%20that%20consultants%20who%20ranked%20below%20average%20benefitted%20the%20most%20from%20using%20the%20technology.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EConversely%2C%20those%20who%20did%20better%20saw%20fewer%20gains.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20study%2C%20published%20Thursday%2C%20involved%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fpapers.ssrn.com%2Fsol3%2Fpapers.cfm%3Fabstract_id%3D4573321%5C%22%3E758%20BCG%20consultants%20globally%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%94%20or%20about%207%25%20of%20the%20company's%20individual%20contributor-level%20consultants.%20They%20were%20divided%20into%20two%20groups%3A%20one%20with%20access%20to%20GPT-4%2C%20the%20model%20that%20currently%20powers%20ChatGPT%2C%20and%20another%20group%20without.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBefore%20the%20experiment%2C%20the%20staffers%20were%20tested%20to%20gauge%20their%20average%20level%20of%20performance%2C%20classifying%20them%20into%20%26quot%3Bbottom-half%26quot%3B%20and%20%26quot%3Btop-half%26quot%3B%20skilled%20participants.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThey%20were%20then%20assigned%20a%20series%20of%20practical%20consulting%20tasks%20for%20a%20fictional%20shoe%20company%20and%20had%20their%20performance%20graded%20by%20human%20and%20AI%20raters.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20greatest%20gains%20were%20seen%20by%20below-average%20performers%20using%20AI%2C%20whose%20average%20performance%20improved%20by%2043%25.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETheir%20above-average%C2%A0counterparts%20only%20saw%20an%20average%20performance%20increase%20of%2017%25%20from%20using%20AI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20study%20also%20found%20that%20those%20who%20used%20AI%20completed%20their%20tasks%20faster%20and%20produced%20higher-quality%20results%20than%20those%20without%20access.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20it%20also%20underscored%20the%20risks%20of%20over-reliance%20on%20AI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EConsultants%20with%20access%20to%20AI%20performed%20up%20to%2020%25%20worse%20when%20presented%20with%20tasks%20that%20were%20beyond%20the%20AI's%20grasp.%20In%20these%20cases%2C%20the%20AI%20would%20present%20misleading%20yet%20plausible%20responses.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20study%20was%20conducted%20by%20researchers%20from%20Harvard%2C%20MIT%2C%20the%20University%20of%20Warwick%2C%20and%20the%20University%20of%20Pennsylvania%2C%20along%20with%20the%20Boston%20Consulting%20Group.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEthan%20Mollick%2C%20a%20Wharton%20professor%20and%20a%20co-author%20of%20the%20study%2C%20wrote%20in%20a%20post%20on%20X%3A%20%26quot%3BAI%20worked%20like%20a%20leveler%3A%20lower%20performers%20had%20the%20biggest%20gains.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%20data-embed-type%3D%5C%22twitter%5C%22%20data-type%3D%5C%22embed%5C%22%3E%20%3Cblockquote%20data-lang%3D%5C%22en%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22twitter-tweet%5C%22%20data-conversation%3D%5C%22undefined%5C%22%20data-cards%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3E%20%E2%80%94Ethan%20Mollick%20(%40emollick)%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2Fmims%2Fstatuses%2F1703020667308806373%5C%22%3ESeptember%2016%2C%202023%3C%2Fa%3E%20%3C%2Fblockquote%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cp%3EAnother%20study%20%E2%80%94%20published%20in%20April%20%E2%80%94%20examined%20customer%20service%20workers%20at%20a%20Fortune%20500%20company%20and%20found%20that%20highly-skilled%20workers%20saw%20a%C2%A0%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fai-tool-barely-helped-productivity-high-skilled-experienced-workers-study-2023-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%26quot%3Bclose%20to%200%25%26quot%3B%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0productivity%20boost%20with%20an%20AI%20assistant.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20contrast%2C%20lower-skilled%20agents%20saw%20a%20productivity%20boost%20of%2035%25.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETo%20be%20sure%2C%20generative%20AI%2C%20as%20it%20currently%20exists%2C%20remains%20prone%20to%20convincingly%C2%A0%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fai-math-error-flaws-bias-hacker-conference-openai-google-2023-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epresenting%20wrong%20statements%20as%20fact%3C%2Fa%3E.%20The%20fallout%20of%20these%20errors%20can%20be%20severe%20%E2%80%94%20ranging%20from%C2%A0%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fapparently-ai-generated-obituary-headline-nba-player-brandon-hunter-useless-2023-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ebutchered%20obituaries%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0to%C2%A0%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessin