y%20be%20exceedingly%20challenging.%20Consequently%2C%20New%20Delhi%20may%20need%20to%20brace%20itself%20for%20the%20possibility%20of%20a%20turbulent%20relationship%20with%20Mal%C3%A9.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20results%20of%20the%20first%20round%20went%20relatively%20unnoticed%20in%20India%2C%20while%20New%20Delhi%20was%20still%20basking%20in%20the%20afterglow%20of%20the%20G20%20summit.%20On%20September%209%2C%20Maldives%20held%20its%20fourth%20multi-party%20presidential%20election%20with%20the%20largest%20pool%20of%20candidates.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20principal%20opposition%20candidate%20of%20the%20Progressive%20Party%20of%20Maldives-People%E2%80%99s%20National%20Congress%20coalition%2C%C2%A0Mohamed%20Muizzu%20got%2046%25%20of%20the%20votes%2C%20while%20Solih%20came%20second%20with%2039%25%20of%20the%20votes.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAccording%20to%20the%20Maldivian%20electoral%20system%2C%20if%20no%20candidate%20gets%20more%20than%2050%25%2C%20there%20is%20a%20run-off%20between%20the%20top%20two%20candidates.%20On%20September%2030%2C%20Solih%20will%20get%20another%20chance%20to%20improve%20his%20tally%20and%20attempt%20to%20be%20the%20first%20democratically%20elected%20president%20to%20get%20a%20second%20term.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWhile%20the%20polls%20going%20for%20a%20second%20round%20did%20not%20come%20as%20a%20surprise%2C%20the%20substantial%20gap%20in%20votes%20between%20Muizzu%20and%20Solih%20serves%20as%20a%20wake-up%20call.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EOn%20the%20political%20front%2C%20the%20odds%20are%20against%20Solih%20managing%20to%20close%20the%20gap%20with%20Muizzu%20in%20the%20second%20round%20on%20September%2030%2C%20mainly%20because%20the%20same%20factors%20that%20shaped%20the%20outcome%20of%20the%20first%20round%20continue%20to%20exist.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ESince%20the%20first%20multi-party%20presidential%20elections%20in%202008%2C%20the%20turnout%20has%20been%20consistently%20high%2C%20ranging%20from%2085%20to%2091%25.%20In%20the%202018%20presidential%20elections%2C%20it%20stood%20at%2089.22%25.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ciframe%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fflo.uri.sh%2Fvisualisation%2F15040111%2Fembed%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22Interactive%20or%20visual%20content%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3E%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fpublic.flourish.studio%2Fvisualisation%2F15040111%2F%3Futm_source%3Dembed%26utm_campaign%3Dvisualisation%2F15040111%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_top%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20alt%3D%5C%22Made%20with%20Flourish%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fpublic.flourish.studio%2Fresources%2Fmade_with_flourish.svg%5C%22%3E%20%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EOn%20Saturday%2C%20the%20turnout%20was%20just%2079%25%2C%20leading%20the%20Maldivian%20Democratic%20Party-led%20ruling%20coalition%E2%80%99s%20vice-presidential%20candidate%20Mohammad%20Aslam%20claiming%20that%20their%20party%20supporters%20had%20not%20gone%20to%20the%20booths.%20%E2%80%9CThere%20are%2037%2C000%20votes%20we%20did%20not%20receive%2C%E2%80%9D%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen.sun.mv%2F84677%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Ehe%20claimed%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20reason%20for%20apathy%20among%20MDP%20sympathisers%20range%20from%20in-fighting%20to%20anger%20over%20Solih%20not%20acting%20on%20corruption%20charges.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%20third%20place%20in%20the%20first%20round%20of%20polling%20was%20Ilyas%20Labeeb%2C%20the%20presidential%20candidate%20for%20The%20Democrats%20political%20party%2C%20a%20breakaway%20faction%20of%20Maldivian%20Democratic%20Party%20or%20MDP%20led%20by%20former%20president%2C%20Mohamed%20Nasheed.%20He%20got%207%25%20of%20the%20votes%2C%20which%20meant%20that%20if%20the%20MDP%20had%20remained%20united%2C%20the%20ruling%20coalition%E2%80%99s%20candidate%20could%20probably%20have%20been%20in%20a%20competitive%20tie%20with%20the%20opposition%20candidate%20instead%20of%20trailing%20behind.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOnce%20the%20results%20of%20first%20round%20were%20out%2C%20frantic%20negotiations%20for%20alliances%20started%20immediately%20based%20on%20various%20mathematical%20permutations%20of%20votes%2C%20which%20are%20all%20based%20on%20the%20hope%20that%20electoral%20calculations%20done%20on%20paper%20will%20translate%20into%20actual%20results%20on%20election%20day.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EFor%20Solih%2C%20getting%20Nasheed%E2%80%99s%20party%20to%20back%20into%20the%20fold%20would%20be%20the%20best%20option.%20But%2C%20so%20far%2C%20The%20Democrats%20are%20playing%20hard%20to%20get.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EDespite%20their%20long%20political%20and%20personal%20association%2C%20Nasheed%E2%80%99s%20estrangement%20from%20Solih%20is%20rooted%20in%20former%E2%80%99s%20insistence%20of%20changing%20the%20governance%20from%20a%20presidential%20to%20parliamentary%20system.%20Nasheed%20separated%20from%20the%20MDP%20shortly%20after%20Solih%20won%20the%20presidential%20primary%20in%20January%20this%20year.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EHoping%20to%20capitalise%20on%20their%20position%20with%20the%20two%20candidates%20seeking%20to%20attract%20more%20alliances%20to%20boost%20their%20numbers%2C%20The%20Democrats%20have%20demanded%20that%20there%20should%20be%20a%20referendum%20on%20changing%20to%20a%20parliamentary%20system%20before%20the%20September%2030%20runoff%20elections.%20Nasheed%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2FMohamedNasheed%2Fstatus%2F1702610714739998972%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Etweeted%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20on%20Friday%2C%20September%2015%2C%20that%20Solih%20is%20unlikely%20to%20win%20the%20second%20round%20of%20presidential%20polls%20and%20called%20on%20MDP%20members%20to%20reconsider%20the%20powers%20of%20the%20president.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2F671702%2Findia-ibrahim-solih-maldives-presidential-election%2F%5C%22%3EAhead%20of%20Maldives%20Presidential%20Polls%2C%20Solih%20Government%E2%80%99s%20Ties%20With%20India%20Emerge%20as%20Main%20Issue%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20Democrats%E2%80%99%20demand%20for%20an%20immediate%20referendum%20is%20impossible%20to%20implement%20before%20September%2030%2C%20as%20the%20Election%20Commission%20has%20also%20held.%20If%20a%20transition%20to%20parliamentary%20system%20is%20his%20primary%20concern%2C%20it%20is%20also%20not%20clear%20that%20Nasheed%20has%20much%20choice%20to%20change%20things%20at%20this%20point.%20Former%20President%20Abdulla%20Yameen%2C%20head%20of%20the%20Progressive%20Party%20of%20Maldives%2C%20has%20also%20reportedly%20refused%20to%20meet%20Nasheed%20%E2%80%93%20and%20his%20party%20has%20never%20been%20a%20proponent%20of%20dilution%20of%20presidential%20powers.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWhile%20individual%20MDP%20members%20have%20called%20for%20The%20Democrats%20to%20come%20back%2C%20there%20has%20been%20no%20public%20talks%20between%20Solih%20and%20Nasheed%2C%20till%20now.%20The%20Democrats%20have%20also%20pointed%20the%20finger%20at%20MDP%20for%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2Fi%2Ftimeline%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Eattempting%20to%20%E2%80%98buy%E2%80%99%20votes%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20in%20the%20second%20round.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%20contrast%2C%20Solih%20travelled%20and%20stayed%20for%20talks%20for%20two%20days%20at%20the%20resort%20of%20the%20fourth%20runner-up%20%E2%80%93%20business%20tycoon%20and%20veteran%20politician%2C%20Gasim%20Ibrahim%2C%20of%20Jumhoree%20Party%20%E2%80%93%20who%20got%202.47%25%20of%20the%20votes.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EGasim%E2%80%99s%20lacklustre%20performance%20in%20the%20first%20round%20has%20also%20raised%20eyebrows%2C%20as%20he%20was%20thought%20to%20have%20a%20reliable%20voter%20base%20among%20his%20numerous%20resort%20employees.%20While%20he%20has%20previously%20played%20a%20pivotal%20role%20in%20elections%20as%20a%20kingmaker%2C%20his%20influence%20has%20undoubtedly%20waned%20in%20this%20election%20due%20to%20his%20underwhelming%20electoral%20performance.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20opposition%20coalition%20had%20already%20courted%20Gasim%2C%20but%20the%20latter%20has%20yet%20to%20announce%20his%20decision.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20India%20problem%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIt%20was%20notable%20that%20a%20media%20report%20about%20the%20discussions%20claimed%20that%20Gasim%E2%80%99s%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen.sun.mv%2F84706%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Eprimary%20concern%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20with%20President%20Solih%20was%20on%20Maldives%E2%80%99%20relation%20with%20India%20%E2%80%93%20a%20key%20talking%20point%20for%20the%20line-up%20of%20challengers%20during%20the%20campaign.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fsouth-asia%2Findia-ibrahim-solih-maldives-presidential-election%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EAs%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20Wire%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%20had%20reported%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20the%20presidential%20debate%20before%20the%20polls%20signalled%20how%20the%20question%20of%20alleged%20Indian%20troops%20stationed%20in%20Maldives%20was%20repeatedly%20brought%20up%20during%20the%20campaign%20to%20corner%20Solih.%20This%20allegation%20had%20also%20been%20the%20basis%20of%20the%20%E2%80%98India%20Out%E2%80%99%20campaign%20that%20had%20been%20spearheaded%20by%20former%20President%20Abdulla%20Yameen.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWhile%20denials%20went%20out%2C%20President%20Solih%20and%20his%20government%20were%20perceived%20to%20be%20batting%20from%20the%20backfoot%20while%20facing%20the%20relentless%20allegations.%20The%20