.com%2Fhigh-rent-and-job-losses-forced-1-in-8-millennials-to-move-back-in-with-their-parents-this-year%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%20Property%20Management%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Around%2052%25%20of%20millennials%20in%20the%20US%20are%20homeowners%2C%20according%20to%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.investopedia.com%2Fmajority-of-millennials-are-now-homeowners-7378138%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EInvestopedia%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20Hong%20Kong%2C%20it's%20not%20easy%20to%20buy%20a%20home.%20Hong%20Kong%20is%20the%20most%20expensive%20place%20to%20buy%20a%20house%2C%20according%20to%20the%20latest%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn2.hubspot.net%2Fhubfs%2F7049971%2FContent%2520Offers%2FCBRE-Global-Living-2020.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EGlobal%20Living%20Report%20from%20CBRE%3C%2Fa%3E.%20The%20average%20property%20price%20in%20Hong%20Kong%20is%20HK%249.8%20million%20%E2%80%94%20the%20highest%20in%20the%20world.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20I%20buy%20a%20property%20as%20a%20single%20person%2C%20there%20will%20be%20a%20lot%20of%20financial%20pressure%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Ng.%20%26quot%3BThe%20continued%20high%20property%20prices%20make%20me%20feel%20uncomfortable%20and%20deterred%20from%20buying.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAniqah%20Bhatnagar%2C%2027%2C%20was%20born%20in%20India%20and%20moved%20to%20Hong%20Kong%20at%20four%20months%20old%2C%20where%20she%20grew%20up%20and%20currently%20lives.%20With%20a%20permanent%20Hong%20Kong%20Identity%20Card%2C%20she%20works%20for%20a%20US%20law%20firm%20as%20a%20pitch%20specialist.%20She%20lives%20in%20an%20apartment%20with%20her%20mother%20in%20Kwun%20Tong%2C%20an%20area%20in%20east%20Kowloon%20that%20has%20become%20a%20hub%20for%20both%20residential%20and%20commercial%20purposes.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHer%20mother%20owns%20the%20apartment.%20Bhatnagar%20cannot%20speak%20Cantonese%2C%20although%20it%20is%20the%20most%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bycensus2016.gov.hk%2Fen%2FSnapshot-08.html%23%3A~%3Atext%3DCantonese%2520was%2520still%2520the%2520most%2C2006%2520to%252096.7%2525%2520in%25202016.%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecommonly%20used%20language%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20Hong%20Kong.%20English%20is%20the%20co-official%20language%20of%20Hong%20Kong%2C%20and%20more%20than%20half%20the%20population%20can%20speak%20it.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBhatnagar%20said%20her%20long-term%20goal%20is%20to%20buy%20a%20home%20%E2%80%94%20but%2C%20like%20many%20Hong%20Kongers%2C%20Bhatnagar%20is%20finding%20it%20difficult%20to%20get%20her%20foot%20in%20the%20door.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BYou%20have%20to%20have%20saved%20or%20have%20access%20to%20a%20significant%20amount%20of%20liquidity%20for%20a%20down%20payment%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EThey%20are%20focused%20on%20saving%20for%20the%20future.%20%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Wilson%20Ho%20Hong%20Kong%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65014ff6992da60019eb34cc%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22902%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EWilson%20Ho%20looks%20out%20at%20the%20Ngong%20Ping%20360%20Hong%20Kong%20cable%20cars.%3Cp%3EWilson%20Ho%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EWilson%20So%2C%2036%2C%20works%20as%20a%20locksmith.%20He%20runs%20his%20business%20with%20a%20partner%20and%20can%20make%20up%20to%20HK%2450%2C000%20a%20month.%20He%20lives%20with%20his%20wife%20in%20a%20550-square-foot%20home%20in%20Kai%20Tak%2C%20an%20up-and-coming%20part%20of%20the%20city%20with%20new%20high-rises%2C%20and%20pays%20HK%2415%2C000%20a%20month%20in%20rent.%20So%20said%20he%20saves%20about%2030%25%20of%20his%20income%20as%20%26quot%3Breserve%26quot%3B%20cash.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBhatnagar%20said%20she%20tries%20to%20save%2060%20to%2070%25%20of%20her%20salary%2C%20and%20does%20so%20without%20having%20to%20pay%20a%20hefty%20rent%20%E2%80%94%20although%20the%20%26quot%3BAsian%20parent%20gratitude%20fee%20is%20customary%20in%20my%20household%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said%2C%20explaining%20that%20there's%20an%20unspoken%20rule%20in%20Asian%20households%20whereby%20you%20give%20a%20certain%20percentage%20of%20your%20income%20back%20to%20your%20parents%20to%20thank%20them%20for%20raising%20you.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20to%20show%20gratitude%20mainly%2C%C2%A0%20but%20also%20to%20thank%20my%20mother%20because%20I%20don't%20pay%20rent%20in%20a%20terribly%20expensive%20city.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENg%20said%20she%20puts%20her%20savings%20in%20for%20future%20retirement%2C%20though%20it's%20not%20much%20with%20monthly%20savings%20of%20about%20HK%242%2C000%20out%20of%20her%20salary.%20%26quot%3BI%20also%20use%20some%20as%20working%20capital%20for%20travel%20and%20emergencies%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20Hong%20Kong%20protests%2C%20followed%20by%20the%20pandemic%2C%20changed%20the%20city.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cstrong%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%22910%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22hong%20kong%20protest%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F650171b0992da60019eb39b3%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22683%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EA%20protester%20on%20June%2012%2C%202019%20in%20Hong%20Kong%20when%20crowds%20gathered%20in%20central%20Hong%20Kong%20as%20the%20city%20braced%20for%20another%20mass%20rally.%3Cp%3EAnthony%20Kwan%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Hong%20Kong%20protests%20took%20place%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bbc.com%2Fnews%2Fworld-asia-china-49317695%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%20between%202019%20and%202020%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20with%20many%20students%20and%20adults%20taking%20to%20the%20streets%20to%20fight%20back%20against%20the%20government's%20decision%20to%20introduce%20an%20extradition%20bill%20between%20Hong%20Kong%20and%20China.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOver%20six%20months%2C%20clashes%20between%20police%20and%20protestors%20caused%20disruption%20to%20city%20life.%20The%20tourism%20industry%20took%20a%20hit%20during%20this%20period%2C%20and%20the%20pandemic%20arrived%20shortly%20after.%20The%20extradition%20bill%20was%20eventually%20withdrawn.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENg%20said%20she%20has%20noticed%20changes%20in%20the%20city.%20%26quot%3BAfter%20the%20social%20incidents%2C%20the%20freedom%20of%20news%20and%20speech%20has%20indeed%20been%20restricted%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20%26quot%3BNewspapers%20and%20editorials%20that%20once%20openly%20criticized%20the%20government%20and%20political%20figures%2C%20now%20rarely%20speak%20publicly.%20As%20for%20street%20demonstrations%2C%20even%20'outspoken%20people'%20used%20to%20be%20common%2C%20but%20now%20they%20have%20disappeared.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBhatnagar%20doesn't%20see%20herself%20living%20in%20the%20city%20in%20the%20long%20run%2C%20saying%20she's%20looking%20to%20cities%20like%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsingapore-millennial-housing-prices-income-debt-dreams-2023-6%5C%22%3ESingapore%3C%2Fa%3E%20or%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftypical-australian-millennial-16k-student-debt-housing-crisis-2023-7%5C%22%3ESydney%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20as%20she's%20seen%20a%20shift%20in%20the%20job%20market%2C%20which%20is%20now%20more%20limited%20to%20non-Chinese%20speakers.%20That%20being%20said%2C%20the%20large%20exodus%20from%20Hong%20Kong%20during%20the%20protests%20and%20pandemic%20gave%20rise%20to%20more%20job%20opportunities%20in%20the%20market.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPolitically%2C%20Bhatnagar%20leans%20liberal.%20%26quot%3BThe%20protests%20were%20an%20incredibly%20uncertain%20time%2C%20but%20I%20did%20feel%20slightly%20removed%20from%20them%2C%20as%20a%20lot%20of%20the%20nationalism%20that%20was%20in%20the%20atmosphere%20during%20that%20time%2C%20was%20not%20a%20feeling%20I%20shared%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20%26quot%3BHong%20Kong%20has%20changed%20in%20the%20last%20five%20years%20due%20to%20the%20protests%20and%20the%20pandemic%20and%20is%20not%20somewhere%20I%20see%20myself%20long%20term%2C%20but%20that%20is%20not%20a%20direct%20result%20of%20the%20protests%2C%20it%20is%20due%20to%20larger%20issues%20such%20as%20a%20language%20barrier%20in%20the%20career%20workplace.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fbus-research.hkbu.edu.hk%2Fresearchers-centres%2Fprof-xu-huang.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EXu%20Huang%2C%20a%20chair%20professor%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20the%20department%20of%20management%2C%20marketing%2C%20and%20information%20systems%20at%20Hong%20Kong%20Baptist%20University%20said%20that%20younger%20people%20tend%20to%20have%20different%20values%20and%20focus%20on%20self-expression%2C%20%26quot%3BThey're%20more%20willing%20to%20tell%20people%20their%20needs%2C%20what%20they%20want%2C%20and%20ask%20for%20help%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EMany%20Hong%20Kong%20millennials%20tend%20to%20have%20a%20localized%20lens%2C%20Huang%20said%3A%20They%20are%20focused%20on%20local%20job%20opportunities%2C%20local%20issues%2C%20and%20the%20local%20environment.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%22614%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Summer%20Ng%20mountains%20Hong%20Kong%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65028da61afe8f0019ea1df2%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22460%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ESummer%20Ng%2C%2033%2C%20is%20happy%20to%20call%20Hong%20Kong%20home.%3Cp%3ESummer%20Ng%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EMany%20millennials%20choose%20to%20stay%20put%20in%20Hong%20Kong.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BHong%20Kong%20is%20very%20unique%20compared%20to%20other%20European%20countries%20and%20even%20the%20mainland.%20When%20I%20ask%20if%20millennials%20want%20to%20move%20somewhere%2C%20they%20say%20they%20want%20to%20stay%20in%20Hong%20Kong%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Huang.%20%26quot%3BEven%20going%20to%20the%20mainland%20is%20not%20in%20their%20consideration.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20stands%20in%20contrast%20to%20his%20observations%20of%20European%20millennials%2C%20who%20he%20says%20are%20more%20willing%20to%20move.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIn%20many%20European%20countries%2C%20millennials%20are%20looking%20for%20more%20opportunities%20outside%20of%20their%20own%20environments%2C%20reaching%20as%20far%20as%20Asia%20or%20South%20America%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Huang.%20%26quot%3BHong%20Kong%20locals%2C%20in%20comparison%2C%20are%20very%20localized%2C%20focusing%20on%20localized%20job%20opportunities%2C%20education%2C%20and%20environment.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20could%20be%20due%20to%20a%20variety%20of%20factors%2C%20including%20the%20fact%20that%20Hong%20Kong%20has%20a%20good%20education%20system%2C%20Huang%20said.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww2.deloitte.com%2Fcn%2Fen%2Fpages%2Fabout-deloitte%2Farticles%2F2019-millennial-survey.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EThe%20Deloitte%20Global%20Millennial%20Survey%202019%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20growing%20up%20in%20a%20world%20of%20accelerated%20transformation%20has%20generally%20left%20millennials%20and%20the%20generation%20after%20them%2C%20Gen%20Zs%2C%20feeling%20unsettled%20about%20the%20future.%20Despite%20global%20economic%20growth%2C%20expansion%2C%20and%20opportunities%2C%20the%20survey%20saw%20these%20youths%20respond%20with%20deep%20declines%20towards%20their%20country's%20social%20and%20political%20climates%2C%20institutions%20like%20the%20government%2C%20the%20media%2C%20and%20business.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20job%20market%20in%20Hong%20Kong%20is%20notoriously%20competitive.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cstrong%3E%3