tps%3A%2F%2Fvariety.com%2F2023%2Ffilm%2Fnews%2Fkorea-box-office-weekend-sleep-2-1235726008%2Famp%2F%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Doubling%20Farmer's%20Income%3A%20A%20Tale%20of%20Empty%20Promises%2C%20Deceit%20and%20Propaganda%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2022%2F02%2F05183719%2FScreenshot-2022-02-05-at-6.37.14-PM.png%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThis%20article%20is%20the%20first%20in%20a%20series%20on%20the%20state%20of%20Indian%20economy%20co-curated%20by%20the%20Centre%20for%20Financial%20Accountability%2C%20New%20Delhi%20and%20The%20Wire.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFarmers%20were%20enticed%20by%20Narendra%20Modi%20and%20the%20Bharatiya%20Janata%20Party%20in%202014%20with%20an%20attractive%20promise%20that%20their%20produce%20would%20be%20procured%20at%20a%20Minimum%20Support%20Price%20(MSP)%20at%20least%20one%20and%20a%20half%20times%20the%20comprehensive%20cost%20of%20production%20according%20to%20the%20C2%2B50%25%20formula.%20The%20relentless%20dinning%20of%20the%20promise%20had%20generated%20hope%20in%20no%20small%20measure%20and%20helped%20sway%20rural%20voters%20in%20many%20states%20in%20favour%20of%20the%20BJP.%20The%20high%20hopes%2C%20however%2C%20burst%20asunder%20when%20the%20Narendra%20Modi-led%20Union%20Government%20filed%20an%20affidavit%20in%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20that%20it%20would%20not%20be%20possible%20to%20determine%20the%20MSP%20according%20to%20its%20promise%20as%20such%20increase%20would%20distort%20the%20market.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20February%2028%2C%202016%2C%20on%20the%20eve%20of%20the%20Union%20Budget%2C%20Prime%20Minister%20Narendra%20Modi%20made%20yet%20another%20promise%20on%20%E2%80%98doubling%20farmers%E2%80%99%20income%E2%80%99%20(DFI)%20by%202022%2C%20as%20India%20completes%2075%20years%20of%20independence.%20A%20year%20later%2C%20at%20the%20peak%20of%20protests%20demanding%20implementation%20of%20the%20promise%20of%20MSP%20at%20C2%2B50%25%2C%20in%20May%202017%2C%20Amit%20Shah%2C%20the%20then%20BJP%20president%2C%20made%20an%20audacious%20claim%20that%20within%20three%20years%20of%20coming%20to%20power%2C%20the%202014%20poll%20promise%20was%20nearly%20fulfilled%20and%20the%20MSP%20was%2043%25%20more%20than%20the%20cost%20of%20production%20if%20the%20cost%20of%20land%20is%20excluded%20from%20the%20price%20calculation.%20He%20also%20asserted%20that%20MSP%20by%20taking%20into%20account%20the%20land%20price%20was%20impossible%20to%20implement.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Ashok%20Dalwai%20Committee%20on%20DFI%20was%20set%20up%20on%20April%2013%2C%202016.%20%C2%A0The%20Committee%20set%20the%20time%20frame%20for%20achieving%20the%20target%20from%202016-17%20to%202022-23%2C%20with%202015-16%20as%20the%20base%20year.%20Extrapolating%20from%202012-13%20NSSO%20estimates%2C%20the%20average%20annual%20income%20of%20the%20farmer%20at%20the%20national%20level%20in%202015-16%20was%20taken%20as%20Rs%2096%2C703%20i.e.%2C%20about%20Rs%208%2C058%20per%20month%20for%20a%20farm%20household.%20The%20targeted%20farmers%E2%80%99%20income%20at%20the%20national%20level%20in%202022-23%20according%20to%20the%20Committee%20was%20to%20be%20Rs%202%2C71%2C378%20at%20current%20prices%20or%20Rs%2022%2C610%20per%20month.%20Achieving%20this%20target%2C%20the%20Committee%20pointed%20out%20in%20its%20report%2C%20required%20a%20farm%20income%20growth%20rate%20of%2010.4%25%20per%20annum.%20However%2C%20the%20committee%20did%20not%20provide%20a%20coherent%20strategy%20of%20providing%20technological%20or%20economic%20support%20to%20farmers%20that%20would%20help%20raise%20yields%20and%20incomes.%20The%20mammoth%20report%20running%20into%2014%20volumes%20did%20not%20say%20anything%20about%20steps%20that%20need%20to%20be%20taken%20to%20ensure%20that%20farmers%20received%20C2%2B50%25%20price%20for%20their%20produce.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20has%20now%20come%20to%20light%20that%20a%20separate%20Special%20Task%20Force%20on%20DFI%20was%20also%20set%20up%20by%20the%20Niti%20Ayog%20in%20January%202018%2C%20acting%20on%20a%20letter%20by%20one%20Sharad%20Marathe%2C%20an%20NRI%20businessman%20with%20no%20known%20expertise%20in%20agriculture%20who%20submitted%20a%20concept%20note%20titled%20%3Cem%3E%E2%80%9CDoubling%20of%20Farmers%E2%80%99%20Incomes%20Through%20Market%20Driven%2C%20Agri%20Linked%20Made%20in%20India%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fem%3E.%20While%20the%20final%20report%20of%20this%20task%20force%2C%20also%20led%20by%20Ashok%20Dalwai%2C%20is%20not%20available%2C%20it%20is%20known%20that%20the%20task%20force%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fagriculture%2Frevealed-the-sinister-corporate-agenda-behind-the-modi-govts-controversial-farm-laws%5C%22%3Eonly%20talked%20to%20select%20private%20companies%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20an%20apparent%20attempt%20to%20identify%20steps%20that%20the%20government%20was%20to%20take%20to%20promote%20interests%20of%20private%20companies%20in%20agriculture%20and%20related%20economic%20activities.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%2077th%20round%20of%20Situation%20Assessment%20Survey%20of%20Agricultural%20Households%20released%20in%202021%20shows%20that%20the%20estimated%20monthly%20income%20of%20farm%20households%20in%202018-19%20was%20merely%20Rs%2010%2C218%20per%20month%20in%20nominal%20terms.%20This%20will%20be%20about%20Rs%201%2C22%2C616%20annually%2C%20which%20although%20midway%20before%20the%20targeted%202022%20deadline%20for%20DFI%2C%20is%20nowhere%20close%20to%20the%20targeted%20income%20of%20Rs%202%2C71%2C378%20at%20current%20prices%20or%20Rs%2022%2C610%20per%20month.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhat%20then%20came%20was%20a%20fig%20leaf%20in%20the%20form%20of%20a%20report%20by%20State%20Bank%20of%20India%E2%80%99s%20Economic%20Research%20Department%20(ERD).%20Claiming%20to%20have%20used%20%E2%80%9Ca%20well-spread%2C%20well-represented%20and%20probabilistic%20sample%20to%20estimate%20the%20change%20in%20income%20from%20FY18%20to%20FY22%20for%20all%20segments%20of%20farmers%2C%20large%20to%20small%20to%20marginal%20ones%E2%80%9D%20based%20on%20primary%20data%20of%20SBI%20agricultural%20portfolio%20across%20states%20and%20%E2%80%9Cgranular%20data%20of%20various%20crops%20from%20agri-intensive%20branches%E2%80%9D%20it%20loudly%20announced%20that%20farmers%E2%80%99%20income%20doubled%20in%20FY22%20as%20compared%20to%20FY18%20for%20certain%20crops%20in%20some%20states%20(like%20soyabean%20and%20sugarcane%20in%20Maharashtra%2C%20cotton%20and%20paddy%20in%20Karnataka%2C%20wheat%20in%20Rajasthan%2C%20and%20groundnut%20and%20cotton%20in%20Gujarat)%2C%20while%20in%20all%20other%20cases%20it%20rose%20in%20the%20range%20of%201.3-1.7%20times.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F11125829%2FUntitled-design-1-2.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F11125829%2FUntitled-design-1-2.jpg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F11125829%2FUntitled-design-1-2-300x169.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F11125829%2FUntitled-design-1-2-1024x576.jpg%201024w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-672506%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22675%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EPM%20Modi%20at%20the%20G20%20Summit%20in%20New%20Delhi.%20In%20the%20background%20are%20farmers.%20Photos%3A%20X%2F%40G20org%20and%20XJ%2FFlickr%20(CC%20BY-NC-ND%202.0)%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20ERD%20did%20not%20come%20up%20with%20an%20explanation%20of%20the%20methodology%2C%20sample%20size%2C%20cost%20calculation%2C%20the%20distribution%20of%20respondents%20across%20different%20classes%20of%20the%20peasantry%2C%20the%20basis%20on%20which%20farmers%E2%80%99%20incomes%20were%20calculated%20or%20why%20Rajasthan%2C%20Gujarat%2C%20Maharashtra%20and%20Karnataka%20were%20chosen%2C%20these%20shoddy%20claims%20unfortunately%20got%20wide%20coverage%20in%20the%20media.%20The%20ERD%20study%20also%20kept%20out%20the%20landless%20tenants%20who%20do%20not%20come%20under%20the%20purview%20of%20crop%20loans.%20Even%20if%20for%20a%20moment%20we%20ignore%20the%20lack%20of%20clarity%20on%20the%20methodology%20used%20and%20the%20fact%20that%20the%20receivers%20of%20bank%20loans%20do%20not%20represent%20the%20entire%20spectrum%20of%20peasantry%2C%20extrapolating%20these%20results%20to%20claim%20that%20farmers%E2%80%99%20incomes%20doubled%20in%202022%20is%20little%20more%20than%20a%20far-fetched%20attempt%20to%20please%20those%20at%20the%20helm.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAny%20observer%20of%20agricultural%20costs%20and%20prices%20knows%20that%20MSP%20is%20mostly%20notional%20as%20there%20is%20no%20assured%20procurement%20in%20most%20cases.%20The%20procurement%20as%20a%20percentage%20of%20total%20production%20in%202021-22%20was%200%25%20for%20soyabean%20and%20as%20low%20as%202.05%25%20for%20groundnut.%20Farmers%20are%20forced%20to%20make%20distress%20sales%20at%20prices%20lower%20than%20the%20MSP%20while%20traders%20make%20a%20killing%20at%20their%20expense%20and%20fleece%20the%20consumers.%20The%20level%20of%20procurement%20of%20paddy%20and%20cotton%20in%20Karnataka%2C%20and%20wheat%20in%20Rajasthan%20is%20very%20negligible%20and%20cannot%20buttress%20the%20claim%20that%20the%20MSP%20announced%20boosted%20farmers%E2%80%99%20incomes%20and%20better%20price%20discovery.%20There%20is%20no%20public%20procurement%20of%20sugarcane%20and%20the%20farmers%20face%20a%20unique%20situation%20of%20delivering%20their%20harvest%20but%20not%20receiving%20payment%20from%20corporate%20sugar%20mills%2C%20leading%20to%20mounting%20arrears%20in%20thousands%20of%20crores.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELet%20us%20now%20look%20at%20the%20ground%20reality.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20MSP%20for%20the%20Kharif%20season%202023-24%20announced%20on%20June%207%2C%202023%20claiming%20to%20%E2%80%9Censure%20remunerative%20prices%E2%80%9D%20and%20%E2%80%9Cencourage%20crop%20diversification%E2%80%9D%20is%20neither%20fair%20nor%20remunerative.%20It%20belied%20the%20hopes%20of%20the%20farmers%20and%20inflicts%20huge%20losses%20in%20their%20incomes.%20Let%20alone%20encouraging%20crop%20diversification%2C%20it%20discourages%20farmers%20from%20investing%20in%20agriculture.%20Rather%20than%20%3Cem%3EDoubling%20Farmers%E2%80%99%20Incomes%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20rising%20input%20costs%20coupled%20with%20unfair%20MSP%20are%20pushing%20large%20sections%20of%20the%20farmers%20especially%2C%20the%20small%2C%20marginal%2C%20middle%20farmers%20as%20well%20as%20tenants%20into%20indebtedness.%20Instead%20of%20C2%2B50%25%2C%20the%20regime%20has%20conveniently%20shifted%20goalposts%20to%20using%20A2%2BFL%20as%20the%20benchmark%20cost%20which%20do%20not%20include%20rental%20value%20of%20owned%20land%20and%20interest%20on%20owned%20fixed%20capital.%20There%20is%20a%20catch%20even%20in%20the%20prices%20calculated%20as%20per%20the%20A2%2BFL%20formula.%20The%20official%20cost%20of%20cultivation%20surveys%20significantly%20understates%20cost%20of%20cultivation%20across%20each%20state%2C%20which%20is%20then%20averaged%20by%20the%20Commission%20of%20Agricultural%20Costs%20and%20Prices%20(CACP)%20to%20compute%20the%20MSP.%20The%20CACP%20document%20%3Cem%3EPrice%20Policy%20for%20Kharif%20Crops%2C%20The%20Marketing%20Season%202023-24%20%3C%2Fem%3Eadmits%20that%20the%20estimates%20of%20projected%20cost%20of%20production%20for%20paddy%20by%20the%20governments%20of%20Andhra%20Pradesh%2C%20Bihar%2C%20Karnataka%2C%20Kerala%2C%20Maharashtra%2C%20Punjab%2C%20Tamil%20Nadu%2C%20Telangana%20and%20West%20Bengal%20are%20higher%20than%20the%20CACP%20projections.%20For%20paddy%2C%20the%20C2%20cost%20projected%20by%20the%20Kerala%20State%20Agricultural%20Department%20is%20Rs%202%2C847%20per%20quintal%2C%20the%20CACP%20projection%20is%20only%20Rs%202%2C338%20per%20quintal.%20The%20Punjab%20state%20projection%20of%20C2%20cost%20for%20paddy%20is%20Rs%202%2C089%20per%20quintal%20while%20the%20CACP%20projects%20it%20as%20only%20Rs%201%2C462%20per%20quintal.%20In%20most%20crops%20the%20state%20projections%20are%20much%20higher%20than%20the%20CACP%20projection.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20CACP%20estimates%20of%20costs%20fail%20to%20adequately%20take%20into%20account%20increasing%20input%20costs%20or%20factor%20in%20the%20inflation.%20The%20%3Cem%3EDouble%20Engine%20Sarkar%20%3C%2Fem%3Eeven%20did%20not%20bother%20to%20take%20the%20recommendations%20of%20states%20ruled%20by%20the%20BJP%20into%20consideration.%20In%20view%20of%20the%20higher%20cost%20of%20production%20in%20Kerala%2C%20the%20LDF%20government%20gives%20about%20Rs%20800%20per%20quintal%20bonus%20for%20paddy%2C%20procuring%20at%20Rs%202%2C850%20per%20quintal.%20Such%20initiatives%2C%20discouraged%20by%20the%20BJP%20government%20on%20the%20ground%20that%20these%20are%20market-distorting%2C%20are%20a%20lifeline%20for%20agriculture%20and%20farmers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEven%20if%20one%20takes%20the%20CACP%20computation%20of%20C2%20costs%20(Rs%201%2C911%20per%20quintal)%20and%20applies%20the%20C2%2B50%25%20formula%20to%20calculate%20the%20MSP%20of%20paddy%2C%20it%20should%20have%20been%20Rs%202%2C866%20per%20quintal.%20The%20MSP%20announced%20as%20per%20(A2%2BFL)%2B50%25%20is%20only%20Rs%202%2C183%20per%20quintal%20or%20about%20Rs%20700%20per%20quintal%20lesser.%20If%20the%20weighted%20average%20of%20C2%20costs%20provided%20by%20the%20states%20(Rs%202%2C139%20per%20quintal)%20is%20taken%20into%20account%2C%20the%20MSP%20would%20have%20been%20Rs%203%2C208.5%20per%20quintal.%20In%20both%20cases%20the%20MSP%20is%20way%20below%20and%20farmers%20will%20accrue%20a%20loss%20of%20Rs%20683.5%20per%20quintal%20and%20Rs%201%2C025.5%20per%20quintal%20respectively.%20A%20farmer%20in%20Andhra%20Pradesh%20with%20a%20productivity%20of%20six%20tonnes%20per%20hectare%20will%20incur%20a%20loss%20of%20Rs%2041%2C010%20per%20hectare%20and%20Rs%2061%2C530%20per%20hectare%20respectively%20at%20these%20costs.%20This%20will%20translate%20into%20a%20loss%20of%20anything%20between%20Rs%209%2C020%20crore%20to%20about%20Rs%2013%2C540%20crore%20per%20season%20for%20farmers%20of%20the%20state%20(paddy%20is%20cultivated%20in%20more%20than%2022%20lakh%20hectares%20in%20AP).%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20case%20of%20cotton%2C%20the%20Telangana%20state%20C2%20projections%20are%20Rs%2011%2C031%20per%20quintal%20while%20the%20CACP%20projections%20are%20only%20Rs%206%2C264%20per%20quintal.%20Even%20if%20we%20take%20the%20CACP%20projection%20of%20C2%20for%20cotton%20(Rs%205%2C786%20per%20quintal)%2C%20the%20C2%2B50%20price%20should%20be%20Rs%208%2C679%20per%20quintal%20while%20the%20government%20announced%20an%20MSP%20of%20only%20Rs%206%2C620%20per%20quintal.%20Taking%20an%20average%20production%20of%2015%20quintal%20per%20hectare%2C%20the%20losses%20will%20be%20Rs%2030%2C885%20per%20hectare.%20As%20per%20the%20state%2C%20C2%2B50%20would%20be%20Rs%2016%2C547%20per%20quintal%20or%20Rs%209%2C927%20per%20quintal%20more%20than%20the%20MSP%20announced.%20That%20would%20mean%20a%20loss%20of%20Rs%201%2C48%2C905%20per%20hectare.%20Given%20that%20the%20state%20has%20an%20acreage%20of%20about%2019%20lakh%20hectares%2C%20the%20losses%20at%20Central%20MSP%20and%20state-proposed%20MSP%20will%20be%20ranging%20from%20about%20Rs%205%2C868%20crore%20to%20Rs%2028%2C291%20crore.%20One%20can%20imagine%20the%20huge%20disincentive%20to%20a%20farmer%20and%20the%20reason%20why%20farm%20suicides%20are%20rising%20in%20the%20cotton%20belt.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20we%20take%20the%20case%20of%20rubber%2C%20in%202011%20a%20farmer%20was%20getting%20Rs%20230%20per%20kg%20and%20recently%20it%20had%20fallen%20to%20Rs%20124%20per%20kg.%20If%20a%20farmer%20with%20one%20hectare%20produces%20on%20an%20average%201%2C500%20kg%2C%20the%20income%20was%20Rs%203%2C45%2C000%20which%20in%202023%20fell%20to%20Rs%201%2C86%2C000%20or%20a%20loss%20of%20Rs%201%2C59%2C000.%20One%20can%20imagine%20the%20losses%20and%20the%20meagre%20returns%20if%20the%20increasing%20costs%20of%20cultivation%20are%20taken%20into%20account.%20Faulty%20trade%20policy%2C%20the%20India%20ASEAN%20Free%20Trade%20Agreement%2C%20import%20at%20zero%20duties%20and%20so%20on%20at%20the%20behest%20of%20corporate%20cronies%20and%20tyre%20manufacturers%20further%20pushed%20farmers%20into%20crisis.%20The%20losses%20suffered%20by%20farmers%20are%20in%20thousands%20of%20crores%20even%20as%20the%20tyre%20manufacturers%20are%20filling%20their%20coffers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2021%2F11%2F20142921%2FIMG_4540.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2021%2F11%2F20142921%2FIMG_4540.jpg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2021%2F11%2F20142921%2FIMG_4540-300x120.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2021%2F11%2F20142921%2FIMG_4540-1024x410.jpg%201024w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-565690%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22480%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EIllustration%3A%20Pariplab%20Chakraborty%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cp%3EFarmers%20are%20caught%20in%20the%20pincer%20of%20low%20unfair%20prices%20for%20their%20produce%20and%20ever%20rising%20input%20costs%20as%20deregulation%20has%20given%20a%20free%20hand%20to%20the%20companies%20to%20fix%20prices%20without%20any%20control.%20Often%20the%20ruse%20used%20is%20that%20increase%20in%20MSP%20will%20increase%20prices%20for%20consumers%2C%20but%20nothing%20is%20done%20to%20stop%20profiteering%20at%20the%20expense%20of%20farmers%20and%20consumers.%20Even%20the%20Dalwai%20Committee%20recognised%20that%20there%20is%20a%20need%20to%20increase%20productivity%20with%20better%20agronomic%20practices%2C%20high%20yielding%20varieties%20and%20keep%20the%20costs%20of%20production%20lower%20by%20providing%20subsidised%20quality%20inputs%20at%20affordable%20rates.%20However%2C%20the%20entire%20thrust%20seems%20to%20be%20at%20the%20behest%20of%20corporate%20companies%2C%20international%20monopolies%20and%20agencies%20as%20well%20as%20individuals%20advocating%20interests%20of%20predatory%20agribusinesses.%20The%20current%20government%20has%20refused%20to%20take%20the%20responsibility%2C%20devise%20a%20strategy%20of%20public%20provisioning%20of%20these%20critical%20forms%20or%20support%2C%20and%20provide%20resources%20for%20meeting%20this%20responsibility.%20The%20policies%20do%20not%20even%20take%20into%20account%20that%20fact%20that%20supporting%20farmers%20and%20agriculture%20is%20of%20strategic%20interest%20for%20food%20security%20of%20the%20country.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EInflicting%20losses%20on%20farmers%20to%20deliberately%20push%20them%20into%20indebtedness%2C%20pauperise%20and%20dispossess%20them%20from%20their%20land%20is%20the%20direction%20in%20which%20the%20BJP%20government%20is%20moving.%20It%20also%20serves%20their%20purpose%20of%20maximising%20profits%20of%20the%20corporate%20companies.%20The%20three%20Farm%20Acts%20and%20the%20amendments%20to%20the%20Electricity%20Act%20are%20all%20part%20of%20the%20game%20plan%20to%20squeeze%20farmers%20out%20of%20cultivation.%20Increasing%20input%20costs%20and%20low%20yields%20and%20low%20prices%20are%20making%20agriculture%20unviable%20for%20farmers.%20It%20has%20been%20raining%20promises%20and%20assurances%20but%20farm%20distress%20is%20deepening%2C%20as%20shown%20by%20nearly%20four%20lakh%20suicides%20by%20farmers%2C%20agricultural%20workers%20and%20migrant%20daily%20wage%20labourers%20in%20last%20decade.%20The%20BJP%20government%20has%20only%20succeeded%20in%20doubling%20farmers%E2%80%99%20woes.%20%E2%80%98Modi%20Ki%20Guarantee%E2%80%99%20is%20for%20corporate%20cronies%20who%20have%20been%20profiteering%20amidst%20farm%20distress%20and%20not%20just%20doubled%20their%20wealth%20but%20seen%20manifold%20increase.%20It%20has%20only%20sown%20death%20and%20destruction%20in%20farmers%E2%80%99%20lives.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EVijoo%20Krishnan%20is%20a%20writer%20and%20General%20Secretary%20of%20All%20India%20Kisan%20Sabha%20and%20tweets%20at%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3Cem%3E%40VijooKrishnan.%C2%A0%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1695000649000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2022%2F02%2F05183719%2FScreenshot-2022-02-05-at-6.37.14-PM.png%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fagriculture%2Fdoubling-farmers-income-a-tale-of-empty-promises-deceit-and-propaganda%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Far%20from%20seeing%20doubled%20incomes%2C%20farmers%20are%20caught%20in%20the%20pincer%20of%20low%20unfair%20prices%20for%20their%20produce%20and%20ever%20rising%20input%20costs.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fagriculture%2Fdoubling-farmers-income-a-tale-of-empty-promises-deceit-and-propaganda%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22I%20have%20a%20dream%20for%20Telangana%2C%20says%20Sonia%20Gandhi%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1694999604000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.toiimg.com%2Fphoto%2Fmsid-103742521%2Cimgsize-56098.cms%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fcity%2Fhyderabad%2Fi-have-a-dream-for-telangana-says-sonia-announces-six-guarantees%2Farticleshow%2F103742507.cms%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Congress%20parliamentary%20party%20chairperson%20Sonia%20Gandhi%20on%20Sunday%20invoked%20the%20party's%20role%20in%20Telangana's%20statehood%20and%20echoed%20her%20dream%20of%20a%20Congress%20government%20in%20the%20poll-bound%20state%2C%20while%20announcing%20six%20guarantees%20for%20the%20people.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22ROUSHAN%20ALI%22%2C%22e