%20medium-%20to%20long-term%20may%20face%20increased%20competition%20from%20%E2%80%94%20or%20eventual%20absorption%20by%20%E2%80%94%20other%20PMCs%20closely%20associated%20with%20Russia's%20Ministry%20of%20Defense%2C%20such%20as%20PMC%20Convoy%20and%20PMC%20Redut%2C%26quot%3B%20Orr%20said%2C%20referring%20to%20private%20military%20companies.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EReports%20suggest%20those%20other%20groups%20recently%20began%20%26quot%3Brecruiting%20for%20potential%20operations%20in%20Africa%2C%20where%20they%20could%20compete%20with%20Wagner%20and%20eventually%20have%20the%20option%20of%20phasing%20out%20Wagner%20entirely%20%E2%80%94%20which%20would%20further%20serve%20the%20purpose%20of%20reinforcing%20the%20Kremlin's%20control%2C%26quot%3B%20Orr%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOther%20reporting%20indicates%20Russian%20military%20officials%20began%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nytimes.com%2F2023%2F09%2F08%2Fworld%2Feurope%2Fprigozhin-wagner-russia-africa.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emoving%20to%20assume%20control%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20Wagner%20operations%20and%20shore%20up%20relations%20with%20partners%20in%20the%20Middle%20East%20and%20Africa%20weeks%20before%20Prigozhin's%20death%2C%20doing%20so%20even%20as%20Prigozhin%20toured%20the%20region%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.wsj.com%2Fworld%2Frussia%2Fprigozhin-wagner-plane-crash-last-days-2c44dd5c%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eto%20assert%20control%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20his%20organization.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAnton%20Mardasov%2C%20a%20non-resident%20scholar%20with%20the%20Middle%20East%20Institute's%20Syria%20program%2C%20said%20it%20was%20%26quot%3Bobvious%26quot%3B%20the%20Kremlin%20would%20not%20side%20with%20Prigozhin%20in%20his%20dispute%20with%20the%20Ministry%20of%20Defense%20for%20several%20reasons%2C%20including%20%26quot%3Bthe%20specific%20alignment%26quot%3B%20of%20Russia%20elites%2C%20%26quot%3Bwhich%20a%20priori%20was%20not%26quot%3B%20with%20Prigozhin.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWagner's%20autonomous%20existence%20was%20ruled%20out%20because%2C%20together%20with%20Prigozhin%2C%20the%20group%20posed%20a%20serious%20danger%20to%20Moscow%2C%26quot%3B%20Mardasov%20told%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BMoreover%2C%20Prigozhin%20violated%20the%20agreement%20from%20the%20very%20beginning%2C%20leaving%20himself%20many%20loopholes%20in%20business%2C%20and%20it%20was%20clear%20that%20he%20would%20not%20sit%20quietly%2C%26quot%3B%20Mardasov%20said%2C%20pointing%20to%20videos%20Prigozhin%20released%20from%20Belarus%20and%20Africa%20in%20the%20weeks%20before%20his%20death%20as%20confirmation.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Russia%20Putin%20Africa%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F650719ccf05aa00019bdcae4%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221361%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EPutin%20with%20African%20leaders%20and%20heads%20of%20delegations%20at%20the%20Russia-Africa%20summit%20in%20St.%20Petersburg%20on%20July%2028.%3Cp%3EALEXEY%20DANICHEV%2FPOOL%2FAFP%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EUnder%20Prigozhin%2C%20Wagner%20amassed%20a%20business%20empire%20using%20lucrative%20concessions%20from%20governments%20and%20backers%20in%20the%20countries%20where%20it%20operated.%20The%20group's%20profitability%20allowed%20it%20to%20sustain%20its%20operations%20in%20sub-Saharan%20Africa%2C%20a%20huge%20benefit%20for%20the%20organization%20and%20something%20Moscow%20will%20likely%20seek%20to%20preserve.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOrr%20said%20Wagner's%20new%20leaders%2C%20or%20the%20group's%20replacement%2C%20will%20likely%20be%20%26quot%3Beven%20more%20keen%20to%20demonstrate%20their%20activities%26quot%3B%20are%20beneficial%20to%20the%20Russian%20state%20instead%20of%20%26quot%3Bserving%20(the)%20parochial%20economic%20interests%20of%20its%20owners.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Kremlin%20sought%20to%20portray%20Prigozhin's%20%26quot%3Balleged%20greed%20and%20selfishness%26quot%3B%20as%20the%20reason%20for%20his%20downfall%2C%20Orr%20said%2C%20and%20consequently%2C%20%26quot%3Breplacement%20groups%20may%20further%20emphasize%20their%20commitment%20to%20the%20common%20task%20of%20furthering%20the%20interests%20of%20the%20Russian%20state.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDespite%20the%20Kremlin's%20years%20of%20denials%2C%20officials%20in%20the%20Middle%20East%20and%20Africa%20saw%20Wagner%20as%20a%20valuable%20partner%20because%20of%20perceptions%20that%20the%20Russian%20government%20backed%20its%20operations%2C%20Orr%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMoscow%20will%20now%20be%20keen%20to%20show%20%26quot%3Bstrong%20backing%26quot%3B%20for%20whichever%20organizations%20replace%20Wagner%2C%20but%20it%20is%20likely%20to%20avoid%20assuming%20formal%20control%20of%20their%20missions%2C%20which%20could%20entail%20deploying%20Russian%20troops%20to%20replace%20the%20mercenaries%2C%20as%20doing%20so%20would%20be%20%26quot%3Bpolitically%20undesirable%26quot%3B%20amid%20the%20war%20in%20Ukraine%2C%20Orr%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMardasov%2C%20who%20is%20also%20a%20military%20affairs%20analyst%2C%20said%20the%20Kremlin%20likely%20believed%20it%20was%20extremely%20unrealistic%20that%20Wagner's%20senior%20leaders%20would%20work%20under%20closer%20government%20oversight%2C%20with%20attempts%20to%20create%20such%20an%20arrangement%20meeting%20%26quot%3Bserious%20resistance%26quot%3B%20from%20Prigozhin%20and%20his%20closest%20people.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%225120%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20fighter%20from%20Russian%20Wagner%20mercenary%20group%20conducts%20training%20for%20Belarusian%20soldiers%20on%20a%20range%20near%20the%20town%20of%20Osipovichi%2C%20Belarus%20July%2014%2C%202023%20in%20this%20still%20image%20taken%20from%20handout%20video.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64baab72006a5e00194a0b95%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222880%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EA%20Wagner%20Group%20member%20conducts%20trains%20Belarusian%20soldiers%20at%20a%20range%20near%20the%20town%20of%20Osipovichi%20in%20Belarus%20on%20July%2014.%3Cp%3EVoen%20Tv%2FBelarusian%20Defence%20Ministry%2FHandout%20via%20REUTERS%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BMoreover%2C%20the%20Wagner%20PMC%20is%20not%20just%20a%20group%20of%20mercenaries.%20It%20is%20a%20structure%20based%20on%20a%20number%20of%20Prigozhin's%20business%20assets%2C%20which%20has%20political%20strategists%2C%20consulting%2C%20intelligence%2C%20and%20so%20on%2C%26quot%3B%20Mardasov%20said.%20%26quot%3BIt%20is%20impossible%20to%20simply%20change%20the%20owner%20since%20military%20intelligence%20will%20not%20engage%20in%20consulting%20and%20political%20technologies%2C%20and%20for%20the%20SVR%20%5BRussia's%20foreign%20intelligence%20service%5D%2C%20such%20a%20huge%20power%20tool%20is%20redundant.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPrigozhin's%20death%20has%20already%20affected%20Russia's%20position%20in%20Syria%20and%20other%20countries%2C%20including%20in%20Libya%2C%20a%20hub%20for%20Wagner's%20operations%20in%20Africa%20and%20where%20Russian%20military%20leaders%20are%20reportedly%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.wsj.com%2Fworld%2Fafrica%2Frussia-seeks-to-expand-naval-presence-in-the-mediterranean-b8da4db%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eseeking%20naval%20access%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20now%2C%20the%20mercenaries%20have%20some%20leverage%2C%20as%20their%20departure%20would%20create%20a%20gap%20that%20Moscow%20is%20still%20unsure%20how%20to%20fill%20%26quot%3Bsince%20there%20is%20essentially%20no%20real%20working%20plan%20to%20replace%20Wagner%20with%20an%20expeditionary%20force%26quot%3B%20from%20PMCs%20over%20which%20the%20military%20has%20more%20influence%2C%20Mardasov%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20Wagner%20and%20other%20PMCs%20rely%20on%20Russia's%20Ministry%20of%20Defense%20for%20transportation%20and%20oth