mur%20anti-ballistic%20missile%20interceptor%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65075a09f05aa00019bdd54d%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22800%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EA%20transport%20and%20reloading%20vehicle%20for%2051T6%20long-range%20interceptor%20missiles%2C%20part%20of%20the%20A-135%20Amur%20anti-missile%20defense%20complex.%3Cp%3EYuriy%20Shipilov%2FMil.ru%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Gazelle%20is%20an%20endo-atmospheric%20missile%2C%20meaning%20it%20only%20hits%20missiles%20once%20they%20are%20inside%20the%20Earth's%20atmosphere%2C%20at%20altitudes%20of%20less%20than%2060%20miles.%20This%20is%20actually%20the%20inner%20defensive%20ring%3A%20The%20A135%20system%20originally%20had%20an%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.globalsecurity.org%2Fwmd%2Fworld%2Frussia%2Fgorgon.htm%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eouter%20ring%20of%2051T6%20Gorgon%20missiles%3C%2Fa%3E%20with%20megaton-class%20warheads.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20A135%20is%20the%20successor%20to%20the%20A35%20built%20in%20the%201960s%2C%20as%20Russia's%20equivalent%20of%20the%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fminutemanmissile.com%2Fsafeguardcomplex.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EUS%20Safeguard%20system%3C%2Fa%3E%20with%20its%20Sprint%20and%20Spartan%20nuclear-tipped%20interceptors.%20The%20big%20difference%20is%20while%20Safeguard%20was%20positioned%20to%20protect%20US%20ballistic%20missiles%20in%20North%20Dakota%20from%20a%20Soviet%20first%20strike%2C%20the%20A135%20exists%20entirely%20to%20protect%20the%20Russian%20leadership.%20And%20while%20Safeguard%20was%20shut%20down%20in%201976%2C%20the%20A135%20remains%20very%20much%20active.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Gorgon%20silos%20were%20mothballed%20in%202002%2C%20but%20in%20recent%20years%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.globalsecurity.org%2Fwmd%2Fworld%2Frussia%2Fa-235.htm%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EMoscow%20has%20been%20working%20on%20upgrades%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20transform%20the%20A135%20into%20the%20A235%2C%20integrating%20it%20with%20other%20assets%20and%20adding%20new%20long-range%20missiles%20to%20shoot%20down%20satellites%20as%20well%20as%20ballistic%20missiles.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20A135%20is%20sophisticated%2C%20with%20several%20arrays%20of%20radar%20to%20detect%2C%20locate%2C%20identify%20and%20track%20incoming%20threats%2C%20but%20has%20been%20useless%20for%20small%20drone%20attacks%3A%20you%20cannot%20use%20a%20ten-kiloton%20nuclear%20weapon%20against%20a%20low%20altitude%20target.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20wrong%20threat%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221333%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22moscow%20drone%20attack%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64bfa542ed4f46001962d80e%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221000%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EA%20building%20in%20Moscow%20damaged%20in%20a%20drone%20attack%20on%20July%2024.%3Cp%3ESefa%20Karacan%2FAnadolu%20Agency%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EMoscow's%20integrated%20air-defense%20system%20is%20also%20equipped%20to%20deal%20with%20smaller%20threats%2C%20in%20theory.%20The%201st%20Air%20Defense%20Army%20operates%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftass.ru%2Farmiya-i-opk%2F11947633%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ethe%20S-50M%20anti-aircraft%20defense%20complex%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20defend%20the%20capital%20with%20networked%20radars%20and%20batteries%20of%20S-400%20and%20S-300PM2%20surface-to-air%20missile%20launchers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20problem%20is%20that%20the%20drones%20are%20both%20literally%20and%20metaphorically%20not%20on%20its%20radar.%20The%20system%20is%20designed%20to%20tackle%20large%20jets%20and%20cruise%20missiles%20moving%20at%20high%20speed.%20It%20is%20not%20configured%20for%20slow%2C%20low-altitude%20threats.%20In%20fact%20air-defence%20radar%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.flightglobal.com%2Fmilitary-uavs%2Fadjusted-radar-settings-likely-behind-rash-of-usas-unknown-object-detections%2F152026.article%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etypically%20filters%20out%20slow-moving%20objects%3C%2Fa%3E%20as%20these%20are%20likely%20to%20be%20flocks%20of%20birds.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENobody%20in%20the%20Russian%20leadership%20ever%20seems%20to%20have%20thought%20drones%20would%20be%20a%20problem.%20As%20a%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcepa.org%2Farticle%2Fmoscow-near-defenseless-against-drones%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epaper%20by%20the%20think%20tank%20Center%20For%20European%20Policy%20Analysis%20notes%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20%26quot%3BNeither%20the%20National%20Security%20Strategy%20of%202021%20nor%20the%20Military%20Doctrine%20of%20the%20Russian%20Federation%20of%202014%20identify%20drones%20as%20a%20threat%20to%20national%20security.%20The%20Concept%20of%20the%20Development%20of%20the%20Aerospace%20Defense%20of%20the%20Russian%20Federation%20until%202030%2C%20dated%20April%202%2C%202019%2C%20also%20pays%20no%20attention%20to%20countering%20drones.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20has%20left%20a%20massive%20blind%20spot%20which%20needs%20filling.%20Ironically%20enough%2C%20Moscow%20no%20longer%20has%20the%20capacity%20to%20stop%20drones%20with%20performance%20similar%20to%20those%20biplanes%20in%201918.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EPanic%20measures%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Russia%20Moscow%20Pantsir%20air-defense%20system%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64fdc5893d3923001977bbee%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221333%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EA%20Pantsir%20air-defense%20system%20on%20the%20roof%20of%20the%20Ministry%20of%20Defense%20in%20Moscow%20in%20March.%3Cp%3ESTR%2FNurPhoto%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20far%20back%20as%20this%20January%2C%20Russian%20planners%20realized%20that%20Moscow%20was%20wide%20open%20to%20drone%20attacks.%20Ukraine%20had%20been%20building%20small%20drones%20from%20commercial%20kits%2C%20like%20the%20Chinese%20Mugin-5%2C%20and%20packing%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fedition.cnn.com%2F2023%2F03%2F16%2Feurope%2Fchina-made-drone-downed-eastern-ukraine-hnk-intl%2Findex.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ethem%20with%20explosives%20for%20kamikaze%20missions%20in%20Crimea%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMoscow%20lies%20less%20than%20300%20miles%20from%20the%20nearest%20point%20in%20Ukraine.%20Kyiv%20had%20refrained%20from%20attacking%20Russian%20soil%20due%20to%20Western%20sensitivities%2C%20but%20it%20seemed%20inevitable%20that%20the%20massive%20Russian%20missile%20and%20drone%20attacks%20on%20Ukraine%20would%20draw%20a%20response%20and%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.forbes.com%2Fsites%2Fdavidhambling%2F2022%2F04%2F12%2Fa-drone-doolittle-raid-how-ukraine-could-hit-moscow%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Edrone%20strikes%20were%20an%20obvious%20possibility%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERussian%20authorities%20responded%20by%20hoisting%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22http%3A%2F%2Froe.ru%2Feng%2Fcatalog%2Fair-defence-systems%2Fair-defense-systems-and-mounts%2F%2522Pantsir-S1%2522%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ESA-22%20Pantsir%20vehicles%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20to%20the%20roofs%20of%20high-profile%20buildings%20in%20Moscow%2C%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmediacenter.org.ua%2Fpantsir-units-installed-on-the-roofs-of-buildings-in-moscow-is-a-last-resort-weapon-efficacy-of-which-is-questionable-iurii-ihnat%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eincluding%20the%20Defense%20Ministry%3C%2Fa%3E.%20The%20Pantsir%20is%20a%20self-contained%20anti-aircraft%20system%2C%20mounted%20on%20an%20eight-wheeled%20Kamaz%20truck.%20It%20has%20radar%2C%20twin%2030mm%20rapid-fire%20anti-aircraft%20guns%20and%20up%20to%20twelve%20launchers%20for%20surface-to-air%20missiles%20with%20a%20range%20of%2011%20miles.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20slightly%20comic%20sight%20of%2030-ton%20vehicles%20perched%20on%20rooftops%20may%20have%20been%20intended%20to%20reassure%20the%20population%20that%20Moscow%20was%20ready%20to%20defend%20itself.%20But%20commentators%20doubted%20how%20much%20protection%20the%20Pantsirs%20would%20provide.%20They%20had%20performed%20badly%20in%20action%20in%20Syria%20and%20Libya%20where%2C%20embarrassingly%20enough%2C%20Pantsirs%20were%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.realcleardefense.com%2Farticles%2F2020%2F06%2F19%2Flibya_a_catastrophe_for_russias_pantsir_s1_air_defense_system_115394.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Edestroyed%20by%20the%20drones%3C%2Fa%3E%20they%20were%20supposed%20to%20be%20defending%20against.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%202018%2C%20a%20critical%20article%20in%20the%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fnationalinterest.org%2Fblog%2Fbuzz%2Fdoes-russias-anti-drone-pantsir-s1-system-even-work-91251%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ERussian%20military%20journal%20Arsenal%20of%20the%20Fatherland%3C%2Fa%3E%20claimed%20that%2C%20%26quot%3BIn%20Syria%2C%20it%20turned%20out%20that%20the%20Pantsir%20was%20practically%20incapable%20of%20detecting%20low-speed%20and%20small-sized%20targets%2C%20which%20include%20military%20UAVs%20%5Bdrones%5D.%20At%20the%20same%20time%2C%20the%20complex%20regularly%20recorded%20false%20targets%20%E2%80%94%20large%20birds%20flying%20around%20the%20base%20%E2%80%94%20rather%20confusing%20the%20operators.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20drone%20siege%20of%20Moscow%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Moscow%20Russia%20skyscraper%20drone%20attack%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64fb812e3d39230019774356%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221333%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EInvestigators%20examine%20a%20damaged%20skyscraper%20in%20Moscow's%20business%20district%20after%20a%20reported%20drone%20attack%20on%20July%2030.%3Cp%3EAP%20Photo%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20first%20drones%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.theguardian.com%2Fworld%2F2023%2Fmay%2F30%2Fmoscow-drone-attack-mayor-reports-minor-damage-to-buildings%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehit%20Moscow%20in%20May%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20with%20waves%20of%20subsequent%20attacks%20continuing%20through%20July%2C%20August%20and%20September.%20After%20each%20strike%20the%20Russian%20authorities%20invariably%20claim%20that%20they%20brought%20all%20the%20attacking%20drones%20down%20with%20electronic%20warfare%20or%20anti-aircraft%20weapons%2C%20and%20that%20any%20damage%20is%20caused%20by%20falling%20debris.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20are%20good%20reasons%20to%20doubt%20this.%20The%20fact%20that%20the%20same%20high-rise%20building%2C%20which%20houses%20three%20Russian%20government%20ministries%2C%20was%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.reuters.com%2Fworld%2Feurope%2Fdrones-target-moscow-high-rise-building-hit-2023-08-01%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Estruck%20twice%20by%20drones%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20three%20days%20suggests%20that%20the%20damage%20is%20far%20from%20random.%20The%20destruction%20of%20aircraft%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thedrive.com%2Fthe-war-zone%2Fil-76-cargo-jet-left-burning-from-drone-strike-deep-inside-russia%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eat%20nearby%20airbases%3C%2Fa%3E%20also%20suggests%20the%20drones%20are%20getting%20through.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20explains%20the%20latest%20round%20of%20developments.%20As%20the%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2FDefe