0also%20increasing%2C%20with%20malnutrition%20associated%20with%20both%20undernutrition%20and%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov%2Fpmc%2Farticles%2FPMC8820192%2F%5C%22%3Ean%20expanding%20epidemic%20of%20obesity%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0still%20to%20be%20overcome.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20the%20halfway%20point%20for%20the%20implementation%20of%20the%20SDGs%20there%20is%20a%20compelling%20need%20to%20take%20stock%20of%20the%20progress%20towards%20targets%2C%20assess%20the%20challenges%20and%20recommit%20to%20achieving%20the%20goals.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.un.org%2Fen%2Fconferences%2FSDGSummit2023%5C%22%3Emeeting%20in%20September%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0will%20do%20just%20that%20and%20low-%20and%20middle-income%20countries%2C%20which%20constitute%20the%20vast%20majority%20of%20the%20global%20population%2C%20must%20lead%20this%20effort%2C%20with%20support%20from%20other%20nations.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20SDG-3%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fsdgs.un.org%2Fgoals%2Fgoal3%5C%22%3Ehealth%20and%20well-being%20for%20all%20at%20all%20ages%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0was%20adopted%20in%202015.%20It%20overcame%20the%20limitations%20of%20the%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.who.int%2Fnews-room%2Ffact-sheets%2Fdetail%2Fmillennium-development-goals-(mdgs)%5C%22%3EMillennium%20Development%20Goals%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Three%20of%20those%20eight%20goals%20focused%20on%20health%20but%20still%20failed%20to%20cover%20many%20of%20the%20world%E2%80%99s%20major%20health%20challenges%20including%20non-communicable%20diseases%2C%20mental%20health%20disorders%2C%20injuries%20and%20substance%20abuse.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fanalysing-emergency-response-a-basic-assessment-of-helplines-in-india%5C%22%3EAnalysing%20%E2%80%98Emergency%20Response%E2%80%99%3A%20A%20Basic%20Assessment%20of%20Helplines%20in%20India%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EComprehensive%20primary%20care%2C%20espoused%20by%20the%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.who.int%2Fteams%2Fsocial-determinants-of-health%2Fdeclaration-of-alma-ata%5C%22%3EAlma%20Ata%20declaration%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0of%201978%2C%20was%20cast%20aside%20for%20selective%20primary%20care%20and%20vertical%20programmes%20that%20were%20mainly%20donor-driven.%20Vertical%20programmes%20typically%20focus%20on%20a%20specific%20condition%20or%20group%20of%20health%20problems%20and%20often%20have%20only%20short%20or%20medium-term%20goals.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.who.int%2Fhealth-topics%2Funiversal-health-coverage%23tab%3Dtab_1%5C%22%3EUniversal%20health%20coverage%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0was%20not%20considered%20an%20essential%20function%20of%20national%20health%20systems.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20SDG%20agenda%20overcomes%20these%20distortions%20by%20adopting%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.who.int%2Four-work%2Flife-course%5C%22%3Ea%20life-course%20approach%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0that%20gives%20priority%20to%20all%20major%20problems%20undermining%20health%20and%20well-being.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESDG-3%20also%20identified%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.who.int%2Fhealth-topics%2Funiversal-health-coverage%23tab%3Dtab_1%5C%22%3Euniversal%20health%20coverage%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0as%20the%20broad%20platform%20that%20could%20deliver%20health%20services%20while%20offering%20financial%20protection%20against%20inordinate%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fread.oecd-ilibrary.org%2Fsocial-issues-migration-health%2Fhealth-at-a-glance-2009%2Fburden-of-out-of-pocket-health-expenditure_health_glance-2009-62-en%23page1%5C%22%3Eout-of-pocket%20expenditures%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0and%20debilitating%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fread.oecd-ilibrary.org%2Fsocial-issues-migration-health%2Fhealth-at-a-glance-2009%2Fburden-of-out-of-pocket-health-expenditure_health_glance-2009-62-en%23page1%5C%22%3Ecatastrophic%20health%20expenditures%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThese%20expenditures%20were%20imposed%20by%20severe%20and%20often%20acute%20health%20conditions%20that%20called%20for%20hospital%20care%20and%20costly%20interventions.%20Their%20chronic%20burdens%20can%20push%20people%20%E2%80%94%20or%20sink%20them%20deeper%20%E2%80%94%20into%20debt-ridden%20poverty.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.who.int%2Fhealth-topics%2Funiversal-health-coverage%23tab%3Dtab_1%5C%22%3EUniversal%20health%20coverage%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20when%20adequately%20financed%20and%20efficiently%20delivered%2C%20offers%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.who.int%2Fhealth-topics%2Funiversal-health-coverage%23tab%3Dtab_1%5C%22%3Emuch-needed%20protection%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0through%20high%20levels%20of%20population%20coverage%2C%20service%20coverage%20and%20cost%20coverage.%20Affirmation%20of%20comprehensive%20primary%20care%20as%20the%20lead%20vehicle%20of%20the%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.who.int%2Fhealth-topics%2Funiversal-health-coverage%23tab%3Dtab_1%5C%22%3Euniversal%20health%20coverage%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0convoy%20came%20as%20a%20clarion%20call%20in%20the%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.who.int%2Fpublications%2Fi%2Fitem%2Freport-of-the-global-conference-on-primary-health-care-from-alma-ata-towards-universal-health-coverage-and-the-sustainable-development-goals%5C%22%3EAstana%20Declaration%20of%202018%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBetween%202015%20and%202019%2C%20low-%20and%20middle-income%20countries%20started%20working%20towards%20the%20Sustainable%20Development%20Goals.%20However%2C%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.who.int%2Fpublications%2Fi%2Fitem%2F9789290209881%5C%22%3Eprogress%20was%20slow%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0in%20many%20countries%20due%20to%20under-resourced%20health%20systems%2C%20shortages%20of%20skilled%20health%20workers%20and%20a%20hangover%20of%20restrictive%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thelancet.com%2Fjournals%2Flancet%2Farticle%2FPIIS0140-6736(97)90079-9%2Ffulltext%5C%22%3Evertical%20programmes%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0still%20attuned%20to%20preset%20donor%20priorities.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EYet%20there%20have%20been%20some%20successes%20too.%20India%20saw%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Findia-news%2Fmaternal-mortality-ratio-drops-to-97-in-2018-2020-from-130-in-2014-2016-3564201%5C%22%3Ea%20sharp%20decline%20in%20maternal%20mortality%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0(from%20407%20maternal%20deaths%20per%20100%2C000%20live%20births%20in%202000%20to%2097%20during%202018-20).%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdhsprogram.com%2Fpubs%2Fpdf%2FFR375%2FFR375.pdf%5C%22%3EInfant%20mortality%20rates%20halved%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0from%2053.6%20deaths%20per%201%2C000%20live%20births%20in%202006%20to%2026.6%20in%202023.%20Under-five%20mortality%20fell%20too.%20These%20declines%20became%20sharper%20after%20the%20launch%20of%20the%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov%2Fpmc%2Farticles%2FPMC3026119%2F%5C%22%3ENational%20Rural%20Health%20Mission%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0in%202005.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20health%20system%20efforts%20on%20newly%20adopted%20priorities%2C%20like%20non-communicable%20diseases%20and%20mental%20health%2C%20were%20still%20struggling%20to%20gather%20momentum.%20The%20burden%20of%20non-communicable%20diseases%20continued%20to%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thelancet.com%2Fjournals%2Flancet%2Farticle%2FPIIS0140-6736(17)32804-0%2Ffulltext%5C%22%3Espiral%20up%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20initially%20in%20urban%20areas%2C%20but%20later%20engulfing%20rural%20populations%20as%20well.%20Those%20trends%20have%20continued%20over%20recent%20years%20in%20India%20and%20other%20South%20Asian%20countries.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20emergence%20of%20the%20COVID-19%20pandemic%20continued%20to%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.who.int%2Fpublications%2Fi%2Fitem%2F9789290209881%5C%22%3Ehamper%20progress%20towards%20SDG-3%20targets%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0in%20low-%20and%20middle-income%20countries.%20Health%20system%20resources%20were%20focused%20mostly%20on%20combating%20and%20containing%20the%20virus%20and%20saving%20lives.%20Other%20health%20services%20were%20sidelined%20or%20stalled%20and%20critical%20health%20efforts%20related%20to%20SDGs%20were%20deprioritised.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fenvironment%2Fnitrogen-oxides-emissions-increasing-in-south-asia-says-soga-report%5C%22%3EWith%20Delhi%20Atop%20List%20of%20PM2.5%20Exposed%20Cities%2C%20Nitrogen%20Oxide%20Emissions%20Also%20Rise%20in%20South%20Asia%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThese%20issues%20are%20especially%20acute%20in%20low-%20and%20middle-income%20countries.%20There%20are%2014%20countries%20in%20the%20Asia-Pacific%20region%20where%20maternal%20mortality%20rates%20are%20higher%20than%20the%20regional%20average%20and%20likely%20to%20fall%20short%20of%20the%20SDG%20target%20of%20fewer%20than%2070%20maternal%20deaths%20per%20100%2C000%20live%20births%20by%202030.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20United%20Nations%20Population%20Fund%20review%20of%202020%20found%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.who.int%2Fpublications%2Fi%2Fitem%2F9789240068759%5C%22%3Eeven%20higher%20rates%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0than%20previously%20recorded%20because%20of%20the%20COVID-19%20pandemic.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGlobal%20attention%20is%20still%20on%20pandemic%20prevention%2C%20preparedness%20and%20response%2C%20with%20microbial%20surveillance%20and%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.who.int%2Fhealth-topics%2Fone-health%23tab%3Dtab_1%5C%22%3EOne%20Health%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0%E2%80%94%20an%20approach%20that%20recognizes%20the%20health%20of%20people%20being%20closely%20connected%20to%20the%20health%20of%20animals%20and%20environments%20%E2%80%94%20emerging%20as%20major%20themes%20of%20ongoing%20global%20health%20discourse.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERevision%20of%20the%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.who.int%2Fpublications%2Fi%2Fitem%2F9789241580496%5C%22%3EInternational%20Health%20Regulations%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0and%20a%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.who.int%2Fnews-room%2Fquestions-and-answers%2Fitem%2Fpandemic-prevention--preparedness-and-response-accord%5C%22%3Enew%20pandemic%20accord%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0are%20on%20course%20for%20adoption%20in%202024%20under%20the%20auspices%20of%20the%20World%20Health%20Organization.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.who.int%2Fnews-room%2Ffact-sheets%2Fdetail%2Fantimicrobial-resistance%5C%22%3EAntimicrobial%20resistance%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0is%20another%20looming%20major%20public%20health%20threat.%20It%20is%20now%20being%20packed%20into%20the%20pandemic%20preparedness%20agenda%2C%20as%20evident%20from%20the%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.g20.org%2Fcontent%2Fdam%2Fgtwenty%2Fgtwenty_new%2Fdocument%2FG20_HMM_Outcome_Document_and_Chair_Summary.pdf%5C%22%3Eoutcome%20document%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0of%20the%20G20%20Health%20Ministers%E2%80%99%20Meeting%20in%20August%202023.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20declaration%20also%20recognises%20the%20threats%20posed%20to%20health%20by%20climate%20change%20and%20calls%20for%20climate-resilient%20and%20climate-smart%20health%20systems.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWith%20seven%20years%20left%20to%20meet%20the%20SDG%20targets%2C%20the%20world%20must%20focus%20on%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3Eprimary%20care-led%20universal%20health%20coverage%3B%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3Emulti-sectoral%20actions%20across%20other%20SDGs%20to%20steer%20policies%20and%20programmes%20that%20will%20enable%20and%20not%20erode%20overall%20health%3B%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3Eactive%20engagement%20of%20communities%20in%20all%20stages%20of%20health%20policies%20and%20programmes%3B%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3Eincreasing%20global%20access%20to%20technologies%20that%20can%20protect%2C%20preserve%20and%20restore%20health%20%E2%80%94%20such%20as%20vaccines%2C%20diagnostics%20and%20drugs%20%E2%80%94%20without%20being%20hampered%20by%20profit-hungry%2C%20patent-restrictive%20practices%3B%20and%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3Eresearch%20and%20innovation%20that%20can%20identify%20and%20evaluate%20new%20methods%20to%20improve%20health%20system%20performance%2C%20such%20as%20digital%20technologies.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EThese%20call%20for%20increased%20national%20and%20global%20financing%20for%20health%20systems%20and%20health-related%20multi-sectoral%20actions.%20It%20is%20futile%20to%20think%20of%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdocuments1.worldbank.org%2Fcurated%2Fen%2F979591495652724770%2Fpdf%2F115271-REVISED-FINAL-IWG-Report-3-5-18.pdf%5C%22%3Efinancing%20for%20health%20security%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0that%20is%20defined%20only%20in%20terms%20of%20acute%20events.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESince%20population%20health%20is%20the%20best%20overall%20indicator%20of%20success%20across%20all%20SDGs%2C%20global%20policymakers%20must%20give%20more%20funding%20to%20the%20health%20sector%20and%20health-relevant%20programmes%20in%20other%20sectors.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EImproved%20governance%20measures%20need%20to%20also%20ensure%20efficiency%20gains%20for%20money%20spent.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EExpansion%20of%20the%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fapps.who.int%2Firis%2Fbitstream%2Fhandle%2F10665%2F250368%2F9789241511131-eng.pdf%5C%22%3Ehealth%20workforce%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0must%20also%20be%20a%20priority.%20A%20recent%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fpubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov%2F35760437%2F%5C%22%3Eestimate%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0indicates%20that%20a%2015%20million%20shortage%20in%20the%20global%20health%20workforce%20in%202020%20will%20reduce%20to%2010%20million%20by%202030%20but%20with%20much%20slower%20progress%20in%20the%20WHO%E2%80%99s%20African%20and%20Eastern%20Mediterranean%20regions.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20there%20is%20great%20danger%20that%20high-income%20countries%20with%20ageing%20populations%20will%20increasingly%20recruit%20health%20workers%20from%20low-%20and%20middle-income%20countries%2C%20weakening%20the%20latter%E2%80%99s%20health%20systems.%20High-income%20countries%20must%20co-invest%20with%20low-%20and%20middle-income%20countries%20to%20educate%20and%20train%20the%20health%20workers%20in%20those%20countries.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20health%20workforce%20expansion%20must%20involve%20all%20categories%20of%20health%20workers%2C%20the%20greatest%20attention%20must%20be%20paid%20to%20those%20needed%20in%20primary%20care%2C%20which%20is%20pivotal%20to%20achieve%20Goal%203%20targets.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20is%20sufficient%20global%20evidence%20on%20the%20impactful%20and%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fequityhealthj.biomedcentral.com%2Farticles%2F10.1186%2Fs12939-021-01615-y%5C%22%3Eequity-promoting%20capabilities%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0of%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov%2Fpmc%2Farticles%2FPMC4785041%2F%5C%22%3Ecommunity%20health%20workers%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0in%20improving%20maternal%20and%20child%20health%2C%20non-communicable%20diseases%2C%20mental%20health%20and%20pandemic%20response.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20need%20to%20scale%20up%20and%20skill%20up%20this%20transformational%20component%20of%20the%20health%20workforce.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20can%20only%20hope%20that%20the%20policymakers%2C%20international%20organisations%20and%20development%20partners%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.un.org%2Fen%2Fconferences%2FSDGSummit2023%5C%22%3Emeeting%20in%20September%202023%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0to%20review%20progress%20on%20the%20SDGs%20will%20take%20the%20necessary%20steps%20to%20make%20this%20commitment.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cb%3EK.%20Srinath%20Reddy%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Ci%3E%C2%A0is%20an%20honorary%20distinguished%20professor%20at%20the%20Public%20Health%20Foundation%20of%20India.%20He%20is%20the%20former%20president%20of%20the%20foundation%20and%20formerly%20headed%20the%20Department%20of%20Cardiology%20at%20All%20India%20Institute%20of%20Medical%20Sciences%20(AIIMS).%20Professor%20Reddy%20is%20a%20member%20of%20the%20Leadership%20Council%20of%20the%20UN%20Sustainable%20Development%20Solutions%20Network%20(SDSN)%20and%20chairs%20the%20Thematic%20Group%20on%20Health%20for%20the%20SDSN.%20He%20is%20also%20a%20member%20of%20the%20Global%20Panel%20on%20Agriculture%20and%20Food%20Systems%20for%20Nutrition.%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3EThis%20article%20is%20part%20of%20a%20special%20report%20on%20the%20%E2%80%98State%20of%20the%20SDGs%E2%80%99%2C%20produced%20in%20partnership%20with%20the%C2%A0%3C%2Fi%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.unsdsn.org%2F%5C%22%3E%3Ci%3EUN%20Sustainable%20Development%20Solutions%20Network%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Ci%3E%C2%A0(SDSN).%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3EOriginally%20published%20under%C2%A0%3C%2Fi%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcreativecommons.org%2Flicenses%2Fby%2F4.0%2F%5C%22%3E%3Ci%3ECreative%20Commons%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Ci%3E%C2%A0by%C2%A0%3C%2Fi%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2F360info.org%2F%5C%22%3E%3Ci%3E360info%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Ci%3E%E2%84%A2.%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1694943051000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F03%2F26180632%2F2018_5img22_May_2018_PTI5_22_2018_000132B.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fhealth%2Fhealth-must-be-fast-tracked-for-2030%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20COVID-19%20pandemic%20might%C2%A0no%20longer%20be%20a%20public%20health%20emergency%C2%A0but%20the%20world%20is%20still%20facing%20a%20crisis%20in%20health%2C%20and%20progress%20on%C2%A0Sustainable%20Development%20Goal%203%20is%20under%20threat.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A10%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fhealth%2Fhealth-must-be-fast-tracked-for-2030%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Sidbi%20to%20raise%20Rs%2010%2C000%20cr%20from%20rights%20issue%20to%20expand%20equity%20capital%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1694941341000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fbsmedia.business-standard.com%2F_media%2Fbs%2Fimg%2Farticle%2F2020-11%2F25%2Ffull%2F1606298327-6701.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Ffinance%2Fnews%2Fsidbi-to-raise-rs-10-000-cr-from-rights-issue-to-expand-equity-capital-123091700385_1.html%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20lender's%20loan%20growth%20optimism%20comes%20from%20the%20demand%20for%20direct%20financing%20that%20is%20growing%20by%20leaps%20and%20bounds%2C%20which%20two%20years%20ago%20was%20only%207%20per%20cent%20of%20its%20book%20but%20is%20now%2014%20per%20cent%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A1%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Ffinance%2Fnews%2Fsidbi-to-raise-rs-10-000-cr-from-rights-issue-to-expand-equity-capital-123091700385_1.html%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-business--standard-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Famp%2Ffinance%2Fnews%2Fsidbi-to-raise-rs-10-000-cr-from-rights-issue-to-expand-equity-capital-123091700385_1.html%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Famp%2Ffinance%2Fnews%2Fsidbi-to-raise-rs-10-000-cr-from-rights-issue-to-expand-equity-capital-123091700385_1.html%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22On%20its%20One-Year%20Anniversary%2C%20Memories%20of%20Nine%20Deaths%20Hang%20Over%20Project%20Cheetah%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F17142504%2FScreenshot-2023-09-17-at-2.24.53-PM.png%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%3Cstrong%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20As%20Project%20Cheetah%2C%20India%E2%80%99s%20ambitious%20intercontinental%20cheetah%20translocation%20programme%2C%20enters%20its%20second%20year%20on%20Sunday%2C%20the%20Union%20government%20plans%20to%20import%20more%20big%20cats%20that%20do%20not%20have%20thick%20winter%20coats.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ELast%20year%20on%20his%20birthday%2C%20September%2017%2C%20in%20a%20spectacle%2C%20Prime%20Minister%20Narendra%20Modi%20turned%20the%20cheetah%20translocation%20project%20which%20had%20been%20in%20the%20works%20for%20a%20decade%2C%20into%20a%20personal%20project%20and%20released%20eight%20cheetahs%20from%20Namibia%20into%20the%20Kuno%20National%20Park%20in%20Madhya%20Pradesh.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EOn%20February%2018%2C%20the%20second%20batch%20of%20cheetahs%20arrived%20in%20India%20from%20South%20Africa.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EOf%20the%2020%20African%20cheetahs%20brought%20from%20Namibia%20and%20South%20Africa%2C%20six%20adults%20and%20three%20cubs%20have%20died.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ES.P%20Yadav%2C%20Additional%20Director%20General%20of%20Forests%20at%20the%20Environment%20Ministry%2C%20said%20that%20one%20of%20the%20major%20challenges%20faced%20in%20the%20first%20year%20of%20managing%20cheetahs%20in%20India%20was%20the%20%E2%80%9Cunexpected%20development%E2%80%9D%20of%20winter%20coats%20in%20some%20cheetahs%20during%20the%20Indian%20summer%20and%20monsoon%2C%20in%20anticipation%20of%20the%20African%20winter%20(June%20to%20September).%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CSome%20cheetahs%20did%20not%20develop%20winter%20coats%20and%20remained%20infection-free.%20They%20are%20better%20suited%20to%20Indian%20conditions.%20Therefore%2C%20in%20our%20next%20cheetah%20import%2C%20we%20will%20be%20very%20careful%20in%20animal%20selection.%20We%20will%20prefer%20animals%20that%20either%20do%20not%20develop%20winter%20coats%20or%20develop%20thinner%20ones%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20was%20quoted%20as%20saying%20to%20Press%20Trust%20of%20India.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EYadav%20said%20that%20the%20winter%20coats%20along%20with%20high%20humidity%2C%20temperatures%20caused%20itching%20in%20the%20animals%20and%20subsequently%20led%20to%20bruising%20and%20exposed%20skin%20where%20flies%20laid%20eggs%20resulting%20in%20maggot%20infestations%2C%20infections%20and%20septicemia%20leading%20to%20deaths.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAs%20the%20project%2C%20which%20has%20since%20been%20mired%20in%20controversy%20since%20the%20beginning%2C%20enters%20its%20second%20year%2C%20Yadav%20said%20that%20this%20time%20the%20focus%20will%20be%20on%20breeding%20cheetahs%20on%20Indian%20soil.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20first%20thing%20that%20comes%20to%20my%20mind%20is%20the%20breeding%20of%20cheetahs.%20And%20if%20we%20can%20expect%20more%20litter%2C%20the%20cubs%20born%20on%20Indian%20soil%20can%20better%20adapt%20to%20Indian%20situations.%20Once%20the%20breeding%20takes%20place%2C%20we%20will%20understand%20how%20the%20population%20will%20behave%20in%20our%20country.%20So%2C%20the%20main%20thing%20next%20year%20will%20be%20more%20cubs%20on%20the%20soil%20of%20Bharat%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20said.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3ECheetah%20deaths%20mired%20in%20controversy%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWhile%20the%20government%20is%20planning%20to%20import%20and%20breed%20more%20cheetahs%2C%20the%20project%20itself%20has%20been%20mired%20in%20controversy%20because%20of%20the%20deaths%20of%20the%20big%20cats%20on%20Indian%20soil.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EOn%20August%202%20this%20year%2C%20Tiblisi%20%E2%80%93%20aka%20Dhatri%2C%20a%20female%20brought%20to%20Kuno%20from%20Namibia%20was%20found%20dead%2C%20becoming%20the%20the%20sixth%20adult%20cheetah%20to%20die%2C%20from%20the%20cheetahs%20brought%20as%20part%20of%20Project%20Cheetah.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EPrior%20to%20that%20two%20males%20Tejas%20and%20Suraj%20died%20on%20July%2011%20and%2014.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWhile%20experts%20on%20the%20Cheetah%20Project%20Steering%20Committee%20had%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fenvironment%2Fninth-cheetah-dies-in-kuno-national-park%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Esaid%20to%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20Wire%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20%3Cspan%3Ethat%20the%20animals%20died%20due%20to%20radio%20collar-caused%20infections%2C%20the%20National%20Tiger%20Conservation%20Authority%20(NTCA%2C%20which%20implements%20Project%20Cheetah)%20claimed%20that%20all%20cheetahs%20died%20due%20to%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fenvironment%2Fauthorities-say-recent-cheetah-deaths-due-to-natural-causes-mp-chief-wildlife-warden-transferred%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9Cnatural%20causes%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20the%20very%20next%20day.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ELater%20on%20July%2020%20the%20Environment%2C%20Forest%20and%20Climate%20Change%20ministry%20in%20a%20reply%20in%20parliament%20said%20that%20three%20cheetahs%20%E2%80%93%20Daksha%2C%20Tejas%20and%20Suraj%20%E2%80%93%20had%20died%20due%20to%20%E2%80%9Ctraumatic%20shock%E2%80%9D%20without%20mentioning%20what%20caused%20the%20traumatic%20shock.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20three%20cubs%20died%20from%20heat%20stress%2C%20according%20to%20official%20records.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3EAccording%20to%20experts%2C%20several%20deaths%20could%20have%20been%20avoided.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CIn%20India%20we%20had%20dedicated%20veterinary%20support%20and%20intensive%20post%20release%20monitoring.%20It%20was%20assumed%20that%20these%20two%20factors%20would%20minimise%20the%20mortality%20rate%20next%20to%20zero%2C%20at%20least%20in%20the%20initial%20part%20of%20the%20project%20till%20the%20animals%20are%20released%20in%20the%20wild%2C%E2%80%9D%20said%20Adrian%20Tordiffe%2C%20a%20veterinary%20wildlife%20specialist%20at%20the%20University%20of%20Pretoria%20and%20a%20former%20foreign%20consultant%20on%20the%20project%2C%20told%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.deccanherald.com%2Findia%2Fdeaths-cast-shadow-over-project-cheetah-anniversary-2688528%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3E%20Deccan%20Herald%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%20%E2%80%9CAs%20it%20turned%20out%2C%20most%20of%20them%20died%20in%20the%20acclimatisation%20camp.%20This%20was%20a%20setback.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20project%20has%20also%20remained%20controversial%20because%20of%20the%20lack%20of%20information%20being%20shared%20with%20experts%20as%20per%20their%20claims.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EA%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fproject-cheetah-media-gag-order%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Egag%20order%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3Ewas%20also%20issued%20on%20officials%20involved%20in%20Project%20Cheetah%20which%20prevents%20them%20from%20speaking%20to%20the%20press%20on%20any%20information%20regarding%20the%20project.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%20July%2C%20Tordiffe%20had%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fenvironment%2Fproject-cheetah-deaths-radio-collar-infections%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3E%20told%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%3Cem%3EThe%20Wire%3C%2Fem%3E%20that%20communication%20between%20the%20Indian%20and%20South%20African%20teams%20was%20a%20concern.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EOne%20issue%20was%20the%20level%20of%20veterinary%20care%20available%20at%20Kuno%3B%20another%20was%20the%20lack%20of%20a%20senior%20scientist%20at%20Kuno%20to%20coordinate%20the%20management%20and%20monitoring%20of%20the%20animals%20after%20scientist%20Y.V.%20Jhala%20%E2%80%93%20who%20was%20leading%20the%20project%20on%20the%20ground%20%E2%80%93%20was%20forced%20to%20retire%2C%20he%20had%20said.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CWe%20had%20mortality%20from%20factors%20that%20could%20have%20been%20avoided%20with%20better%20supervision%2C%20expertise%2C%20and%20coordination%20with%20experts%2C%E2%80%9D%20%3Cem%3EDeccan%20Herald%3C%2Fem%3E%20quoted%20Jhala%20as%20saying.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3E%E2%80%9CPrestige%20issue%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%20July%2C%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20had%20questioned%20the%20Union%20government%20about%20the%20deaths%20of%20big%20cats%20and%20asked%20why%20it%20was%20such%20a%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fprestige-issue-supreme-court-cheetah-deaths%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9Cprestige%20issue%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20It%20also%20asked%20why%20the%20cheetahs%20were%20all%20released%20in%20Kuno%20National%20Park%20in%20Madhya%20Pradesh%2C%20and%20not%20spread%20out%20across%20sites.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20Union%20in%20its%20affidavit%20to%20the%20court%20told%20the%20apex%20court%20that%20the%20deaths%20are%20%E2%80%9Ctroubling%E2%80%9D%20but%20%E2%80%9Cnot%20unduly%20alarming%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20reply%20was%20filed%20after%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20asked%20for%20a%20detailed%20affidavit%20explaining%20the%20reasons%20for%20the%20cheetah%20deaths%2C%20and%20the%20remedial%20measures%20being%20taken%2C%20be%20submitted.%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20centre%20also%20said%20that%20a%20provisional%20diagnosis%20of%20the%20cheetah%20deaths%20%E2%80%9Cpoints%20towards%20natural%20causes%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1694940954000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F17142504%2FScreenshot-2023-09-17-at-2.24.53-PM.png%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fon-its-one-year-anniversary-memories-of-nine-deaths-hang-over-project-cheetah%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22According%20to%20officials%2C%20one%20of%20the%20major%20challenges%20faced%20in%20the%20first%20year%20of%20managing%20cheetahs%20in%20India%20was%20the%20%E2%80%9Cunexpected%20development%E2%80%9D%20of%20winter%20coats%20in%20some%20of%20them.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A26%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fon-its-one-year-anniversary-memories-of-nine-deaths-hang-over-project-cheetah%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Late%20Iranian%20Activist%20Mahsa%20Amini%E2%80%99s%20Family%20Barred%20From%20Marking%20Her%20First%20Death%20Anniversary%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F09%2F17132823%2Fe52036fc-5334-48c6-810f-305ab71d7e95.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20family%20of%20Jina%20Mahsa%20Amini%2C%20a%